    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-03-18T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-03-18T20:00:00-05:00" n="25"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d25">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1–GE/3–1954: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Korea</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_BEO1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Briggs</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential<lb/>priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Seoul</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-03-19T10:00:00+09:00"
                            >March 19, 1954—10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>913. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 739, March 17. Secretary’s
                    letter which I marked confidential delivered this morning to Foreign Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> who said he would immediately
                    convey it to President <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName>. Only comment
                        <persName corresp="#p_PYT1">Pyun</persName> made while reading letter was in
                    regard to third paragraph (re Russia not “sponsoring power” and declaring
                    conference two sided) with which he apparently disagrees. He also observed it
                    might be “inconvenient” send representative to Washington, assuming Korea
                    decides to attend, and asked why necessary consultation could not be conducted
                    here between him and me.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BEO1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Briggs</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
